                            <comment id="53948" author="mark.fisher" created="Thu, 20 May 2010 03:16:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We can add that feature there, but I guess it would be even better to provide that in the core Spring-JMS module.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="54036" author="jhoare" created="Tue, 25 May 2010 20:49:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;First stab at this, have some test cases too if your interested? I appreciate its not complete as I&apos;m only supporting JMS TextMessage which is fine for our use case, any feedback on improvements wold be welcome.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="54144" author="jhoare" created="Mon, 31 May 2010 19:42:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi, I&apos;ve created this ticket &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.springsource.org/browse/SPR-7250&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://jira.springsource.org/browse/SPR-7250&lt;/a&gt; hoping it can be moved into Spring JMS as you suggested Mark.&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="65597" author="oleg.zhurakousky@springsource.com" created="Fri, 22 Apr 2011 08:17:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;JsonMessageConverter already exists in SI Core module although I can&apos;t seem to locate the original JIRA issue. I think it was part of some other efforts such as &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/browse/INT-1000&quot; title=&quot;Add JSON inbound Messaging Mapper&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;INT-1000&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;INT-1000&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/browse/INT-1001&quot; title=&quot;Add JSON outbound Messaging Mapper&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;INT-1001&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;INT-1001&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="65601" author="oleg.zhurakousky@springsource.com" created="Fri, 22 Apr 2011 08:32:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Taking it back. THe converter I was referring too is in Spring AMQP project&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
